00:35:08.390 --> 00:35:12.290
Because I've actually
wanted a spirit and a mood.

00:35:12.290 --> 00:35:15.650
I imagined a spirit and a
mood of a place to happen,

00:35:15.650 --> 00:35:16.460
and it happened.

00:35:16.460 --> 00:35:19.660
Because I kind of, like, put the
word out and kind of created it

00:35:19.660 --> 00:35:21.140
in the ether in a way.

00:35:21.140 --> 00:35:23.390
Obviously, I wrote things
about how I wanted it to be,

00:35:23.390 --> 00:35:25.556
and I kind of gave interviews,
and things like that.

00:35:25.556 --> 00:35:27.770
But it's actually-- that
spirit has really happened.

00:35:27.770 --> 00:35:29.652
And it's a place of
people of all ages,

00:35:29.652 --> 00:35:30.860
and genders, and sexualities.

00:35:30.860 --> 00:35:34.350
And there's performance, and
there's dance, and it's sexy,

00:35:34.350 --> 00:35:37.980
but it's kind of inclusive
in all sorts of ways.

00:35:37.980 --> 00:35:40.460
And it's just kindness
is the biggest--

00:35:40.460 --> 00:35:42.230
kindness and no judgment
are the kind of--

00:35:45.110 --> 00:35:47.240
We did a screening of the
"Spice World," the movie.

00:35:47.240 --> 00:35:49.730
25th anniversary of "Spice
World," the movie, in which I

00:35:49.730 --> 00:35:51.045
