They'd come up to
give me a note,

00:50:36.270 --> 00:50:37.830
and I'm like,
uh-huh, yeah, what?

00:50:37.830 --> 00:50:38.100
Oh, sure.

00:50:38.100 --> 00:50:38.891
Yeah, I'll do that.

00:50:38.891 --> 00:50:40.150
Yeah, right, OK.

00:50:40.150 --> 00:50:42.430
And it was a really great
thing, because also I

00:50:42.430 --> 00:50:45.280
loved how many people
would post things of it.

00:50:45.280 --> 00:50:48.890
To see me and Bojana, in the
police station, for example,

00:50:48.890 --> 00:50:51.090
me dressed in my sort
of fuddy-duddy way

00:50:51.090 --> 00:50:56.540
rocking out to, like,
Black Box from, like, 1998.

00:50:56.540 --> 00:50:57.530
It's really fun.

00:50:57.530 --> 00:50:58.738
And I think that's the thing.

00:50:58.738 --> 00:51:03.560
You've got to try
and be both things.

00:51:03.560 --> 00:51:07.350
Go straight for that character,
but also retain your own self.

00:51:07.350 --> 00:51:09.280
And again, that's also
the thing but making

00:51:09.280 --> 00:51:11.145
the crew feel that
everyone joins,

00:51:11.145 --> 00:51:12.520
and everyone does
the same thing,

00:51:12.520 --> 00:51:14.780
and everyone feels good
about coming to work.

00:51:14.780 --> 00:51:17.440
Because there's not
many shoots I've

00:51:17.440 --> 00:51:20.830
been on where the leading
actor kind of demands

00:51:20.830 --> 00:51:25.300
that you dance between takes.

00:51:25.300 --> 00:51:25.980
Or you're fired!

00:51:25.980 --> 00:51:29.250
[LAUGHTER]

00:51:29.250 --> 00:51:29.980
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:51:29.980 --> 00:51:33.700
I need to ask you
about "The Good Wife."

00:51:33.700 --> 00:51:37.380
So, big fan of the series,
and, of course, Eli.

00:51:37.380 --> 00:51:40.360
I want to ask you how you
feel about the show ending,

00:51:40.360 --> 00:51:43.690
and also will we see
Eli on the spin-off?

00:51:43.690 --> 00:51:46.330
Because I know his
daughter's there, Melissa.

00:51:46.330 --> 00:51:49.110
But will we see you
in the second season?

00:51:49.110 --> 00:51:51.310
ALAN CUMMING: Ehm,
no, is the answer.

00:51:51.310 --> 00:51:58.030
There was talk of it, but some
technical issues happened.

00:51:58.030 --> 00:52:00.050
See, I feel like--

00:52:00.050 --> 00:52:04.660
I think there's a thing in
America where people aren't

00:52:04.660 --> 00:52:06.322
good about ending things.

00:52:06.322 --> 00:52:08.530
And I think it's all about
sort of-- when something's

00:52:08.530 --> 00:52:13.112
a success, you just
whip it until it falls--

00:52:13.112 --> 00:52:15.320
or until you jump the shark,
that's what you call it,

00:52:15.320 --> 00:52:16.330
doesn't it?

00:52:16.330 --> 00:52:18.470
So I felt like when
"The Good Wife" ended,

00:52:18.470 --> 00:52:20.470
I thought it was the
perfect time for it to end.

00:52:20.470 --> 00:52:22.800
I thought the arc of
the story was great.

00:52:22.800 --> 00:52:24.280
It was the creators
who were still

00:52:24.280 --> 00:52:26.863
working on the show who did that
and ended it how they wanted.

00:52:26.863 --> 00:52:30.166
It wasn't kind of
just, you know--

00:52:30.166 --> 00:52:32.090
in a funny way, I feel
like on television,

00:52:32.090 --> 00:52:33.965
especially on network
television, what you're

00:52:33.965 --> 00:52:35.710
doing is just making
stuff to fill up

00:52:35.710 --> 00:52:37.690
the gaps between
the commercials.

00:52:37.690 --> 00:52:40.600
So when you have a chance
to actually really craft

00:52:40.600 --> 00:52:44.979
something, I think part of the
craft is to kill it as well.

00:52:44.979 --> 00:52:45.520
Or to end it.

00:52:45.520 --> 00:52:46.880
Maybe kill is the wrong word.

00:52:46.880 --> 00:52:49.380
So I was actually really glad
that "The Good Wife" finished.

00:52:49.380 --> 00:52:50.589
I was ready to go as well.

00:52:50.589 --> 00:52:52.380
I was going to leave,
and then they told me

00:52:52.380 --> 00:52:54.380
they were ending it, so I
stayed for the last season.

00:52:54.380 --> 00:52:55.130
So that was great.

00:52:55.130 --> 00:52:56.980
But then when this
spin-off thing came up,

00:52:56.980 --> 00:52:59.140
"The Good Fight,"
and I knew they

00:52:59.140 --> 00:53:01.610
were going to do that, I
was like, oh, that's nice.

00:53:01.610 --> 00:53:05.270
But then when we were shooting
our show, a lot of the people

00:53:05.270 --> 00:53:07.720
were in the same sound stage,
and some of the same crew

00:53:07.720 --> 00:53:08.679
had been working on it.

00:53:08.679 --> 00:53:10.178
I was like, oh, so
what's happening?

00:53:10.178 --> 00:53:10.730
Oh, really?

00:53:10.730 --> 00:53:11.390
Oh.

00:53:11.390 --> 00:53:12.790
Well, my daughter's in it.

00:53:12.790 --> 00:53:13.870
Did they mention me ever?

00:53:13.870 --> 00:53:15.760
Did they mention Eli?

00:53:15.760 --> 00:53:16.680
It was kind of funny.

00:53:16.680 --> 00:53:17.763
It got me all going again.

00:53:17.763 --> 00:53:20.830
And actually it'd be quite
funny to go back and do Eli.

00:53:20.830 --> 00:53:21.871
MISTRAL MYERS: All right.

00:53:21.871 --> 00:53:24.580
Well, in our last minute
or two, without giving away

00:53:24.580 --> 00:53:26.380
too many spoilers,
can you just let

00:53:26.380 --> 00:53:29.530
us know what we should
expect from the upcoming

00:53:29.530 --> 00:53:31.337
season of "Instinct"?

00:53:35.500 --> 00:53:38.790
ALAN CUMMING: At
one point, I shoot

00:53:38.790 --> 00:53:41.830
a glass of poisoned iced tea
out of Whoopi Goldberg's hand,

00:53:41.830 --> 00:53:43.020
thereby saving her life.

00:53:43.020 --> 00:53:44.130
[LAUGHTER]

00:53:44.130 --> 00:53:45.990
How is that?

00:53:45.990 --> 00:53:48.700
MISTRAL MYERS: That is the
perfect way to end this.

00:53:48.700 --> 00:53:50.910
I can't wait to see it.

00:53:50.910 --> 00:53:52.350
ALAN CUMMING:
That's basically it.

00:53:52.350 --> 00:53:54.141
MISTRAL MYERS: Please
give everyone a round

00:53:54.141 --> 00:53:55.660
of applause for our two guests.

00:53:55.660 --> 00:53:59.310
[APPLAUSE]

